<h2>Description</h2>

<p>I have a work container on my device that is managed by an app called Island (made by the greenify developer). Apps within this work container have a little suitcase next to the app icon. When attempting to edit the app icon, Lawnchair crashes and must restart.</p>
<h2>Expected Behavior</h2>

<p>The icon changing menu should appear to select a new icon from a pack.</p>
<h2>Actual Behavior</h2>

<p>Lawnchair Crashes.</p>
<h2>Steps to Reproduce</h2>

<ol>
<li>Have a work container with app installed in it.</li>
<li>Open edit menu</li>
<li>Attempt to change icon</li>
<li>Lawnchair crashes</li>
</ol>
<h2>Environment</h2>






<ul>
<li>Device: Samsung Galaxy S7 Edge</li>
<li>Android version: 7.0</li>
<li>Launcher version: 1.1.0</li>
<li>Rom: Stock Rom</li>
</ul>
